    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The help text in BesuCommand tells exactly what the options are.\r\n```\r\n      --sync-mode=<MODE>     Synchronization mode, possible values are FULL,\r\n                               FAST, X_SNAP (default: FAST if a --network is\r\n                               supplied and privacy isn't enabled. FULL\r\n                               otherwise.)\r\n```\r\nIf something else is specified, I would like a warning message similar to what you get if you specify a network name that's not in the list eg:\r\n```\r\nbesu --network=bogus\r\nInvalid value for option '--network': expected one of [MAINNET, RINKEBY, ROPSTEN, SEPOLIA, GOERLI, KILN, DEV, CLASSIC, KOTTI, MORDOR, ECIP1049_DEV, ASTOR] (case-insensitive) but was 'bogus'\r\n```\r\nSo something like:\r\n\"Invalid value for option '--sync-mode': expected one of ... but was '...'\"",
